divertors/midplane.documentation: Choice of midplane definition (use the lowest index number if more than one value is relevant)

divertors/midplane/index.documentation: Integer identifier (enumeration index within a list). Private identifier values must be indicated by a negative index.

divertors/divertor/name.documentation: Short string identifier (unique for a given device)

divertors/divertor/description.documentation: Description, e.g. “channel viewing the upper divertor”

divertors/divertor/target/name.documentation: Short string identifier (unique for a given device)

divertors/divertor/target/description.documentation: Description, e.g. “channel viewing the upper divertor”

divertors/divertor/target/heat_flux_stea.documentation: Maximum steady state heat flux allowed on divertor target surface (engineering design limit)

divertors/divertor/target/temperature_li.documentation: Maximum surface target temperature allowed to prevent damage (melting, recrystallization, sublimation, etc...)

divertors/divertor/target/t_e_target_spu.documentation: Maximum plasma temperature allowed on the divertor target to avoid excessive sputtering

divertors/divertor/target/power_flux_pea.documentation: Peak power flux on the divertor target surface

divertors/divertor/target/flux_expansion.documentation: Magnetic flux expansion as defined by Stangeby : ratio between the poloidal field at the midplane separatrix and the poloidal field at the strike-point see formula attached, where u means upstream (midplane separatrix) and t means at divertor target (downstream).

divertors/divertor/target/two_point_mode.documentation: Description of SOL according to the two point model, the downstream point being on this target, for various time slices
Heat flux decay length in SOL at divertor entrance, mapped to the mid-plane, this is the lambda_q parameter defined in reference T. Eich et al, Nucl. Fusion 53 (2013) 093031

Heat flux spreading length in SOL at equatorial mid-plane, this is the S power spreading parameter defined in reference T. Eich et al, Nucl. Fusion 53 (2013) 093031. Relevant only for attached plasmas.

divertors/divertor/target/tilt_angle_pol.documentation: Angle between field lines projected in poloidal plane and target, measured clockwise from the target to the projected field lines

divertors/divertor/target/extension_r.documentation: Target length projected on the major radius axis

divertors/divertor/target/extension_z.documentation: Target length projected on the height axis

divertors/divertor/target/wetted_area.documentation: Wetted area of the target, defined by the SOL heat flux decay length (lambda_q) mapped to the target using flux expansion and spreading factor and the target toroidal circumference. In other words, this is the area getting heat flux from the maximum value down to one e-fold decay.

divertors/divertor/target/power_incident.documentation: Power fraction incident on the target (normalized to the total power incident on the divertor)
Total power incident on this target. This power is split in the various physical categories listed below

divertors/divertor/target/power_conducte.documentation: Power conducted by the plasma on this divertor target

divertors/divertor/target/power_convecte.documentation: Power convected by the plasma on this divertor target

divertors/divertor/target/power_radiated.documentation: Net radiated power on this divertor target (incident - reflected)

divertors/divertor/target/power_black_bo.documentation: Black body radiated power emitted from this divertor target (emissivity is included)

divertors/divertor/target/power_neutrals.documentation: Net power from neutrals on this divertor target (positive means power is deposited on the target)

divertors/divertor/target/power_recombin.documentation: Power deposited on this divertor target due to recombination of plasma ions
Power deposited on this divertor target due to recombination of neutrals into a ground state (e.g. molecules)

divertors/divertor/target/power_currents.documentation: Power deposited on this divertor target due to electric currents (positive means power is deposited on the target)

divertors/divertor/target/current_incide.documentation: Total current incident on this target

divertors/divertor/target/tile.documentation: Set of divertor tiles belonging to this target

divertors/divertor/target/tile/name.documentation: Short string identifier (unique for a given device)

divertors/divertor/target/tile/descripti.documentation: Description, e.g. “channel viewing the upper divertor”

divertors/divertor/target/tile/surface_o.documentation: Outline of the tile surface facing the plasma
Toroidal angle (oriented counter-clockwise when viewing from above)

divertors/divertor/target/tile/surface_a.documentation: Area of the tile surface facing the plasma

divertors/divertor/target/tile/current_i.documentation: Total current incident on this tile

divertors/divertor/target/tile/shunt_ind.documentation: If the tile carries a measurement shunt, index of that shunt (in the magnetics IDS shunt array)

divertors/divertor/wetted_area.documentation: Wetted area of the divertor (sum over all targets)

divertors/divertor/power_incident.documentation: Total power incident on the divertor (sum over all targets). This power is split in the various physical categories listed below

divertors/divertor/power_conducted.documentation: Power conducted by the plasma on the divertor targets (sum over all targets)

divertors/divertor/power_convected.documentation: Power convected by the plasma on the divertor targets (sum over all targets)

divertors/divertor/power_radiated.documentation: Net radiated power on the divertor targets (incident - reflected) (sum over all targets)

divertors/divertor/power_black_body.documentation: Black body radiated power emitted from the divertor targets (emissivity is included) (sum over all targets)

divertors/divertor/power_neutrals.documentation: Net power from neutrals on the divertor targets (positive means power is deposited on the target) (sum over all targets)

divertors/divertor/power_recombination_p.documentation: Power deposited on the divertor targets due to recombination of plasma ions (sum over all targets)

divertors/divertor/power_recombination_n.documentation: Power deposited on the divertor targets due to recombination of neutrals into a ground state (e.g. molecules) (sum over all targets)

divertors/divertor/power_currents.documentation: Power deposited on the divertor targets due to electric currents (positive means power is deposited on the target) (sum over all targets)

divertors/divertor/particle_flux_recycle.documentation: Total recycled particle flux from  the divertor (in equivalent electrons)

divertors/divertor/current_incident.documentation: Total current incident on this divertor
